          "code": "\n// ⭐ Starfish Blinking LEDs — SAFE VERSION\n// 6 Orange LEDs: 1 center + 5 arms\n// Each LED has its OWN dedicated pin (~10mA each, well under 20mA limit)\n//\n// Pin Map:\n//   D13 → LED_Center\n//   D12 → LED_Arm1\n//   D11 → LED_Arm2\n//   D10 → LED_Arm3\n//   D9  → LED_Arm4\n//   D8  → LED_Arm5\n//\n// All blink together as one starfish! ⭐\n\nconst int LED_PINS[] = {13, 12, 11, 10, 9, 8};\nconst int NUM_LEDS = 6;\n\nvoid setup() {\n  for (int i = 0; i < NUM_LEDS; i++) {\n    pinMode(LED_PINS[i], OUTPUT);\n  }\n}\n\nvoid loop() {\n  // ⭐ Starfish GLOWS — all LEDs ON together\n  for (int i = 0; i < NUM_LEDS; i++) {\n    digitalWrite(LED_PINS[i], HIGH);\n  }\n  delay(700);\n\n  // 🌑 Starfish SLEEPS — all LEDs OFF together\n  for (int i = 0; i < NUM_LEDS; i++) {\n    digitalWrite(LED_PINS[i], LOW);\n  }\n  delay(300);\n}\n"
        }
      },
